I saw these monster 9 inch spoons being used on the east coast for striper and thought maybe reds would eat them. 
Didn’t really expect it to work! New video on YouTube #fishing #redfish
Couple 25-26’s getting fat and fighting like reds! Fish were gobbling everything up as were getting warmer weather. Caugh on @theslicklure #speckledtrout

Winter trout eat summer trout for breakfast. They’re putting on the weight for winter making them even more fun to go after.
#fishing #speckledtrout
Trout was hanging around schools of reds. Been a streak of great fishing. #speckledtrout

6lber on the slick lure. I’ve always been bad at winter fishing so whenever winter rolls around I focus in on inshore fishing and specifically trout.
 Doesn’t make the most interesting yt content but trout are my favorite fish and maybe in 10 years I’ll be decent! Glad to catch this one. #speckledtrout

One of the best inshore trips of my life with my dad if not the best. 
Started off catching oversized reds on lures 8-14lbs then as the day went on got into some trout. 
Was throwing the slick catching decent trout but as light got lower I slowed down but noticed my dad still catching with the soft-dine xl. I had the same one in my box so I tied it on. Soon after I caught the heaviest trout I’ve measured at 7 and 1/8. Didn’t think I would beat that this year but a few minutes later got a 7 and 1/4 on the same lure. 
Started to question the boga scale lol but verified it was accurate within an ounce or two with a digital scale at home.  Got skunked fishing with friends the next day lolll 
#speckledtrout

Another nice 7lber fishing with dad again. One of my best winters for specklers and I’m not really doing anything different. Just a little luck this year. Caught on warm up after a front on slick lure.  #speckledtrout
She rock hopping on 4 legs. New vid on yt now.

Took my first customer out on a guided trip and he got the biggest fish he ever caught! I get more joy out of guiding others to catch fish rather than catch the myself. 
(Jokes if that isn’t clear)

Thought this one was gonna be a monster because he took forever to get in on the popper. Still good tho 👍
#fishing #jettyfishing

Caught a couple redfish all scraped up around the tail on both sides. Anyone know what causes this? 
.

#redfish #jettyfishing

Seen many big trout being caught on cut bait recently but not by me. Then at the surf this one hit cut ladyfish for me. 
Sadly this 23 incher got hooked deep and was a bleeder. I just wanted some reds! #surffishing #speckledtrout

Very strong year for mangrove snapper. Lots being caught inshore and at the jetties. I wonder why. Good snook year too actually. 
#fishing #jettyfishing
When the current was headed south on the beach the mullet and redfish were cruising along with it! #fishing #surffishing #beachfishing

Redfish in the surf is one of my favorites. Caught on live mullet. New video is live woooo.
